    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN191.2-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ṟaṉṉeñciṟkuc collic celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE prevented going by speaking to his heart.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN191.2">
        <l>attap pātirit tuyttalaip putuvī</l>
        <l>yeriyita ḻalariyō ṭiṭaipaṭa viraii</l>
        <l>veṇṭōṭṭut toṭutta vaṇṭupaṭu kaṇṇit</l>
        <l>tōlputaic ciraṟṟaṭik kōluṭai yumaṇa</l>
        <l>rūrkkaṇ ṭaṉṉa vāram <supplied>vā</supplied>ṅki</l>
        <l>yaruñcura mivarnta nōṉcuval vaṉṟōṭ</l>
        <l>ṭiruntupakaṭ ṭiyampuṅ koṭumaṇi purintavar</l>
        <l>maṭiviṭu vīḷaiyoṭu kaṭiteti rōṭi</l>
        <l>yōmaiyaṅ kāṭṭiṉ varūum vampalark</l>
        <l>kēmañ ceppu meṉṟūḻ nīḷiṭai</l>
        <l>yarumporu ṇacaiip pirintuṟai vallic</l>
        <l>ceṉṟuviṉai yeṇṇuti yāyi ṉaṉṟu</l>
        <l>muraiyiṉi vāḻiye <supplied>ṉe</supplied>ñcē niraimukai</l>
        <l>mullai yaruntu melliya vāki</l>
        <l>yaṟaleṉa virinta vuṟaliṉ cāya</l>
        <l>loliyiruṅ kūnta ṟēṟumeṉa</l>
        <l>valiya kūṟavum vallaiyō maṟṟē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>On the long way in the sun, (10cd)</l>
        <l>where the curved bells that sound on the perfect oxen (7a-c)</l>
        <l>with strong shoulders [and] sturdy necks that climbed the difficult desert, (6)</l>
        <l>dragging the carts, as if they had seen [their] village, (5)</l>
        <l>of the salt merchants, possessing staffs [and] leather-covered, noisy feet, (4)</l>
        <l>with bee-covered chaplets in which white leaves are tied (3)</l>
        <l>to the soft-headed new blossoms of the trumpet flower tree by the road, (1)</l>
        <l>mixing [them] in between with flame-petaled oleander, (2)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">speak of safety (10ab)</l>
        <l>to the strangers that come to the wilderness of toothbrush trees, (9)</l>
        <l>desirously running fast towards [them], with a whistling let go by their cloths, (7df.)</l>
        <l>if, being strong [enough] to stay away, longing for wealth difficult [to make], (11)</l>
        <l>you were to go [and] count on work, (12a-c)</l>
        <l>speak up now, oh my heart. (12d-13c)</l>
        <l>Although you speak harsh [words], would you really have the strength (17)</l>
        <l>to say “we will seek [wealth]!” to [her with] luxuriant dark tresses, (16)</l>
        <l>of a grace sweet to experience that spread like black sand, (15)</l>
        <l>having become soft [and] contain jasmine, with buds in rows. (13df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
